WorkItem.Description:
If you have a function that accepts an object as a parameter for example and you call that method and define the object in the method call, the intellisense does not work on the this keyword. Intellisense refers to this in the context of the object your defining.

Below is code to reproduce.

class test {
    someVariable;

    constructor() {
        this.doWork({
            blah: this.someVariable // try to retype this.someVariable and instellisense doesn't work when typing this.
        });
    }

    doWork(func: any) {

    }
}
